FBIS3-31037 "dreeu030_h_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 HUNGARY Boross Cited on Use of Airspace for B-H Raids LD1102173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1700 GMT 11 Feb 94 LD1102173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] NATO aircraft cannot use Hungary's airspace in case of an aerial bombing attack against Serbs, the BBC quotes Prime Minister Peter Boross. According to the Budapest corrrespondent, the Hungarian Government is concerned that by allowing NATO to use Hungarian airspace for bombing attacks, Hungary would become involved in the war in Yugoslavia, and that the step would also harm the situation of Hungarians in Vojvodina.
